"title": "6030: sin, avoidance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6030: sin, avoidance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God calls his people to avoid sin, and through Jesus Christ gives them the inner power to be victorious over it.</p>\n<h2>God's people are to resist sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:10\">PSA 97:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:23-Prov4:27\">PRO 4:23–4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:34\">1CO 15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:25-Eph5:20\">EPH 4:25–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:21\">JAS 1:21</a></p>\n<h2>The Christian life is a constant struggle against sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13\">HEB 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:14-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:14–7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:10-Eph6:18\">EPH 6:10–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8-1Pet5:9\">1PE 5:8–5:9</a></p>\n<h2>God helps his people to resist sin</h2>\n<h3>Release from sin through Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:7\">ROM 6:1–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11-Col2:12\">COL 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>The avoidance of sin through new life in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:9\">1JN 3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:23\">1PE 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:6\">1JN 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:18\">1JN 5:18</a></p>\n<h2>Believers co-operate with Jesus Christ to avoid sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12-Phil2:13\">PHP 2:12–2:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Believers are to put to death what is sinful in them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:11-Rom6:14\">ROM 6:11–6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to exchange sinful for righteous behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:12-Rom13:14\">ROM 13:12–13:14</a></strong> <em>The words used here, and in similar passages, are those used for “taking off” old clothes and “putting on” new ones.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:22–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:7-Col3:10\">COL 3:7–3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11\">1TI 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:22\">2TI 2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to allow the Spirit to inform and direct their conduct</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:8\">ROM 8:5–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:25\">GAL 5:16–5:25</a></p>\n<h2>Practical steps for overcoming sin and temptation</h2>\n<h3>Meditation on Scripture</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:11\">PSA 119:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:22-Ps18:23\">PSA 18:22–18:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:16–3:17</a></p>\n<h3>Prayerful dependence upon God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:13\">MAT 6:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:13\">PSA 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:41\">MAT 26:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:15–4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Active seeking of the good</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:19\">ROM 6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:14\">PSA 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:16-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:16–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:14-Amos5:15\">AMO 5:14–5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:22\">1TH 5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:11\">3JN 1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Incentives for avoiding sin</h2>\n<h3>The fear of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:6\">PRO 16:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:20\">EXO 20:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:7\">PRO 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:13\">PRO 8:13</a></p>\n<h3>The holiness of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7\">LEV 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:18-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:18–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:7\">1TH 4:7</a></p>\n<h3>The expectation of Jesus Christ's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:7\">1PE 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:9-2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:9–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:4-1Thess5:6\">1TH 5:4–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10-2Pet3:14\">2PE 3:10–3:14</a></p>\n<h3>A consideration of the consequences of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:7-Gal6:8\">GAL 6:7–6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42-Mark9:48\">MRK 9:42–9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:21-Rom6:23\">ROM 6:21–6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:7-Heb6:8\">HEB 6:7–6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26-Heb10:31\">HEB 10:26–10:31</a></p>\n<h3>The need to be a good witness to unbelievers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:15\">1PE 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:2\">1PE 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15-1Pet3:16\">1PE 3:15–3:16</a></p>\n<h2>The role of others in avoiding sin</h2>\n<h3>Bad company is to be avoided</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:33\">1CO 15:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:1–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:10\">PRO 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:13\">1CO 5:1–5:13</a></p>\n<h3>A good example is to be followed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:17\">PHP 3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:9\">PHP 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:1–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:1-1Pet4:3\">1PE 4:1–4:3</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to support one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:19-Jas5:20\">JAS 5:19–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:1-Gal6:2\">GAL 6:1–6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:20\">1TI 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:12\">HEB 3:12</a></p>",
